<subSubSection pageId="167" pageNumber="168" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="167.[151,1436,325,1007]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,325,350]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" reason="1">Redescription.</emphasis>
Forewings 2.0 times longer than wide, length: male 4.0– 
<quantity box="[972,1058,325,349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
(mean = 4.2, n = 3), female 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.3">4.3– 4.7 mm</quantity>
(mean = 4.6, n = 3). Colour light orange; apical parts of facial carinae, subantennal processes, rostrum, sides of pronotum, 2 lateral marks on mesonotum, sides of scutellum, and legs stramineous; fore tibiae and tarsi tinted with orange; hind femora with a faint orange mark; apical half of abdomen orange, but genitalia stramineous (the orange coloration may be faint or absent in some specimens, but not in 
<typeStatus box="[1016,1119,463,487]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">holotype</typeStatus>
). Most forewing veins lined with narrow opaque bands; rest of forewings glassy; veins stramineous to faintly orange-brown, or faintly orange; apex of costa and apical margin orange-red; base of Sc+R with 4 dark spots. Hindwings colourless. In profile junction of vertex and face angulated; subantennal processes connected to margins of facial carinae by a low ridge; rostrum reaching hind coxae. Forewings with Sc+R fork at middle of wing; basal median cell broad, more than twice as wide as basal cell between Sc+R and M; a small triangle at base of Ms1. Male genitalia with pygofer narrow. Genital styles oval; proximal dorsal process short, slender; distal dorsal process long. Apical part of aedeagus with a dorsal, longitudinal groove, and with a pointed lobe on the dorsal right side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1350,741,765]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="167.[151,1436,325,1007]" box="[199,1350,741,765]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis box="[199,333,741,765]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,741,765]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species name is a Latin adjective (
<emphasis box="[775,973,741,765]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[775,899,741,765]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Saccharodite" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">iridipennis</taxonomicName>
, -is, -e
</emphasis>
= with rainbow-coloured wings).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
